Cell[TextData[{
 "US Presidential Obama\[CloseCurlyQuote]s 2008 presidential campaign, 2016 \
campaign to elect  D. Trump to tailor individual messages to individual \
people, target political ads by using Facebook data (without consent), \
meddling of Brexit by Russia. Read article ",
 ButtonBox["Link",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://www.oii.ox.ac.uk/news-events/how-data-and-artificial-\
intelligence-are-actually-transforming-american-elections/"], None},
  ButtonNote->
   "https://www.oii.ox.ac.uk/news-events/how-data-and-artificial-intelligence-\
are-actually-transforming-american-elections/"],
 "? The 2024 Trump campaign used behavioral data and psychographics to \
deliver hyper-specific ads; a \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]suburban mom\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] might receive content focused on school safety, \
while a \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]rural farmer\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] saw \
messages about agricultural deregulation. ",
 ButtonBox["Link",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://designproductmarketing.com/the-2024-campaign-playbook-how-\
data-ai-and-big-bucks-are-redefining-strategy-and-what-marketers-can-learn/#:~\
:text=Let's%20start%20by%20exploring%20the,entirely%20different%20perceptions%\
20of%20reality."], None},
  ButtonNote->
   "https://designproductmarketing.com/the-2024-campaign-playbook-how-data-ai-\
and-big-bucks-are-redefining-strategy-and-what-marketers-can-learn/#:~:text=\
Let's%20start%20by%20exploring%20the,entirely%20different%20perceptions%20of%\
20reality."],
 ". "
}], "Subitem",
