e67288e5848d"],

Cell["\<\
Analysing a dataset about Height ad Weight for American Woman \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.806752791686812*^9, 3.806752814879616*^9}, {
  3.97729396781243*^9, 
  3.9772939680420027`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f787f73a-83d6-40a9-8cd3-\
2724196a8010"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Predicting the data from the model", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.806755641519217*^9, 3.806755645669584*^9}, {
  3.80675573503352*^9, 3.806755738357009*^9}, {3.8067557746129837`*^9, 
  3.806755800361162*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"716a9ca0-91a2-428e-b057-\
eff5960ab681"],

Cell["\<\
What would be the expected weight of an American woman with a height of 57? \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.806754479263768*^9, 3.8067545600726*^9}, {
   3.8539288389401703`*^9, 3.8539288437658987`*^9}, 3.853929111265699*^9},
 FontWeight->"Bold",
 FontVariations->{
 "Underline"->True},ExpressionUUID->"ec0fd81b-9f1d-49b5-8df9-64a27447e571"],

Cell["\<\
We need to extrapolate, using our estimation for the rate of change for lower \
height : for every 1 inch, there is a change of 2 lbs, so we would estimate a \
weight of 115-2=113lbs\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8067545634410048`*^9, 3.806754598425592*^9}, {
  3.806754691836916*^9, 
  3.806754757904434*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5c5de720-6f14-4104-a56a-\
3408a36acda1"],

Cell["\<\
Do the same for an American woman with a height of 73?Answer = 164+5=169!\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812177633295361*^9, 3.8121776722697067`*^9}, {
  3.812190264918118*^9, 3.812190273760244*^9}, {3.843643132585973*^9, 
